.TH MAKNOON 1 "April 2026" "1.3.2" "Maknoon Manual"
.SH NAME
maknoon \- Versatile, ultra-efficient Post-Quantum CLI encryption tool.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B maknoon
[\fIcommand\fR] [\fIflags\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Maknoon (مكنون) is a high-performance encryption tool designed for a post-quantum world. 
It utilizes ML-KEM (Kyber1024) for encryption, ML-DSA (Dilithium87) for signatures, and XChaCha20-Poly1305 for streaming data integrity.
.PP
The tool is built with a 64KB chunk-based streaming architecture, ensuring a constant memory footprint regardless of file size. It features a modular **Profile** system for cryptographic agility, allowing seamless updates to algorithm suites while maintaining backward compatibility. It supports multi-core parallelism for high-speed processing and FIDO2 security keys for hardware-backed master keys.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B keygen
Generate a full Post-Quantum identity (Encryption + Signing keys). Keys are protected by an Argon2id-derived master key. Supports \-\-profile and \-\-profile-file to customize the protection suite.
.TP
.B encrypt [file/dir]
Encrypt a file or directory. If a directory is provided, it is streamed through a TAR encoder and encrypted on-the-fly. Supports \-\-compress (Zstd) and \-\-public-key (ML-KEM).
.TP
.B decrypt [file]
Decrypt and restore data. Automatically detects archive and compression status from the encrypted header. Use \-\-overwrite to bypass safety checks for existing files.
.TP
.B send [file/dir]
Send a file or directory via secure ephemeral P2P (Magic Wormhole). Generates a one-time code and session passphrase. Data is encrypted with a session-specific key before entering the P2P transport.
.TP
.B receive [code]
Receive a file or directory from a peer using the provided code. Requires the session passphrase for decryption.
.TP
.B info [file]
Displays metadata and cryptographic details of an encrypted file (Type, Profile, KEM, SIG, KDF).
.TP
.B identity
Manage Post-Quantum cryptographic identities.
.RS
.TP
.B list
List all local identities.
.TP
.B active
List absolute paths of available public keys for encryption. Useful for automated identity discovery by AI agents.
.TP
.B show [name]
Show details for a specific identity, including hardware binding (FIDO2) status.
.TP
.B rename [old] [new]
Rename an identity and its associated key files.
.RE
.TP
.B sign [file]
Generate a detached Post-Quantum (ML-DSA-87) signature for a file.
.TP
.B verify [file]
Cryptographically verify a file's integrity and origin using a public ML-DSA key.
.TP
.B vault
Manage a secure, encrypted password database (bbolt) protected by Argon2id.
.RS
.TP
.B set [service]
Store a secret. Prompts for the secret via a secure terminal. In JSON/Agent mode, the secret must be provided via the \fBMAKNOON_PASSWORD\fR environment variable.
.TP
.B get [service]
Retrieve a secret from the vault.
.TP
.B list
List all services stored in the vault.
.RE
.TP
.B gen [subcommand]
Generate high-entropy secure credentials.
.RS
.TP
.B password
Generate a random character password. Supports \-\-length and \-\-no-symbols.
.TP
.B passphrase
Generate a mnemonic passphrase. Supports \-\-words and \-\-separator.
.RE
.TP
.B profiles
List built-in cryptographic profiles and the JSON schema for constructing custom profiles. Supports \-\-generate to output a randomized secure profile JSON and \-\-output to save it. Use \-\-overwrite to replace an existing profile file.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-p, \-\-public-key
Path to a recipient's public key (.kem.pub or .sig.pub).
.TP
.B \-k, \-\-private-key
Path to your private key (.kem.key or .sig.key).
.TP
.B \-s, \-\-passphrase
Provide the vault master passphrase non-interactively.
.TP
.B \-c, \-\-compress
Enable Zstd compression before encryption.
.TP
.B \-\-stealth
Enable fingerprint resistance by removing the recognizable magic bytes from the file header. This provides deniability by making the ciphertext indistinguishable from random noise. Requires the same flag for decryption.
.TP
.B \-o, \-\-output
Specify the output file path or directory. Use "-" as the output path to write to standard output.
.TP
.B \-\-overwrite
Force overwrite of existing files during decryption or profile generation.
.TP
.B \-q, \-\-quiet
Suppress progress bars and informational messages.
.TP
.B \-\-json
Output command results in strict JSON format. Suppresses interactive prompts and returns errors as JSON on stderr. In this mode, vault database paths are strictly restricted to the default directory for security.
.TP
.B \-\-profile [id]
Specify a built-in cryptographic profile ID (1: XChaCha20, 2: AES-GCM).
.TP
.B \-\-profile-file [path]
Load a custom cryptographic profile from a JSON file.
.TP
.B \-j, \-\-concurrency
Specify the number of parallel workers for chunk processing (0 for auto-scale).
.TP
.B \-f, \-\-fido2
Use a FIDO2 hardware security key for authentication and key derivation.
.SH SECURITY RATIONALE
.TP
.B XChaCha20-Poly1305
Chosen for superior software performance and resistance to nonce-misuse via its 192-bit nonce.
.TP
.B Argon2id
The gold standard for key derivation, providing robust protection against GPU-based brute-force attacks.
.TP
.B Constant Memory
By processing data in 64KB chunks, Maknoon prevents memory exhaustion and side-channel leakage associated with large memory allocations.
.TP
.B Memory Hygiene
All sensitive buffers (passphrases, raw keys, PINs) are explicitly zeroed out in RAM immediately after use.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.maknoon/keys/
Default directory for storing cryptographic identities.
.TP
.I ~/.maknoon/vaults/
Default directory for password databases.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B MAKNOON_PASSPHRASE
A master passphrase used to unlock keys and vaults non-interactively.
.TP
.B MAKNOON_PASSWORD
The secret value to be stored when using \fBvault set\fR in non-interactive mode.
.TP
.B MAKNOON_JSON
Set to "1" to enable global JSON output mode and suppress interactive prompts.
.TP
.B MAKNOON_AGENT_MODE
Set to "1" to enable automatic agent handshake. If stdout is not a TTY, the tool automatically switches to JSON mode.
.TP
.B MAKNOON_PUBLIC_KEY
Default path to a recipient's public key.
.TP
.B MAKNOON_PRIVATE_KEY
Default path to your private key.
